Market Overview:

Squash is defined as a concentrated syrup prepared using fruits. It is a non-alcoholic syrup that is extensively used in beverage making. Squash drink is prepared by blending the squash with an appropriate amount of carbonated water or water.

Rise in the demand for non-alcoholic products is the major driver escalating the market growth, also increase in the adoption of organic fruit juices as an alternative to aerated drink, rise in the adoption of natural fruit juices as an alternative to aerated drinks by health conscious consumers and increasing in the aware about their shared responsibility towards reduction of plastic pollution are also the factors driving the squash drinks market growth. Moreover, rise in the research and development activities in the market and increase in the technological advancements and modernization in the production techniques will further create new opportunities for the squash drinks market manufacturers in the forecast period of 2021- 2028.

The major players covered in the squash drinks market report are Unilever, Britvic PLC, Hamdard, The Coca-Cola Company, Rasna, Prigat, Primor, SUNTORY HOLDINGS LIMITED and Sunquick among other domestic and global players. Market share data is available for Global, North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific (APAC), Middle East and Africa (MEA) and South America separately. DBMR analyst understands competitive strengths and provides competitive analysis for each competitor separately.

Global Squash Drinks Market Scope

Squash drinks market is segmented on the basis of product type, nature, base types and distribution channel. The growth among various segments helps in the better analyzation of growth and strategies for better vision of market.

On the basis of product type, squash drinks market is segmented into no added sugars and added sugars.
Based on nature, the squash drinks market is segmented into regular and blended.
Based on base types, squash drinks market is segmented into citrus fruits, berry, tropical & exotic fruits and mixed fruit.
Based on distribution channel, the squash drinks market is segmented into super/hypermarket, convenience stores, independent grocery stores and online retailers.
